race.comment: IMPEY (3) was checked in the run when seventh in a Grade 5 at this track last time over 340m, finishing 17 lengths from the winner (20.35). Has Box 3 this time where he has a win. Rates a top chance. WANAKA (1) finished seventh last time at Launceston but could not have been more impressive before that in her powerful 19.35 win at this track over 340m. Top win two back and can measure up again. ASTON WESTERN (8) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by 0.8 lengths at this track in a handy 19.70 beating Rogue Danger. The form from his last run stacks up well. In great form and can continue his winning ways. MISS CHIRPY (7) hasn't been far away, finishing in the money twice in a row including last time in a Grade 5 at Launceston over 278m.
